description: This header file declares the interface for the Persistent Storage Manager's System Registry Object, including function prototypes for creation, removal, initialization, and resetting of the registry, serving as an API for other components.

methods.name: PsmCreateSysRegistry
methods.description: Creates and initializes the system registry object, returning a handle to it.

methods.name: PsmSysroCreate
methods.description: Creates the system registry object with specified context handles.

methods.name: PsmSysroRemove
methods.description: Removes and cleans up the system registry object.

methods.name: PsmSysroEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects for the system registry component.

methods.name: PsmSysroReset
methods.description: Resets the system registry object to default state.
